Date: 16 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AP via the Milwaukeechanel.com [edited]
<http://www.themilwaukeechannel.com/news/4289662/detail.html>

Anthrax scare at Pentagon false alarm
-------------------------------------
The anthrax scare at the Pentagon was a false alarm. Initial tests
indicated the deadly spores might be present at 2 Pentagon mail
facilities. The latest test came back negative. Testing continues
Wednesday [16 Mar 2005] morning, but military officials say they are
confident there is no public threat.
Hundreds of postal workers took antibiotics. 3 mail facilities in
Washington shut down. The White House was on alert, all because of an
apparent mix-up at a military lab.
Government officials now say it does not appear that the mail
facility next to the Pentagon or any other mail rooms were
contaminated with anthrax.
--
