Date: Wed 16 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC [edited]
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/4352383.stm>

AP reported that a sample of anthrax, which was kept for comparison
purposes, may have gotten mixed up with the samples taken from the
mail offices.
"We have no evidence that there was anthrax material in the mail,"
said William Winkenwerder, assistant secretary of defense for health
affairs. "We had some preliminary results that were positive, but
subsequent additional tests have determined that the sample that we
had was in fact negative."
